From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 00:05:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: rockchip: Restore RK3399 6.8 PERST timing

Armbian kernel narrowing showed that RK3399 PCIe works with the 6.8.11
Rockchip64 edge kernel and fails by 6.12.x with:

    rockchip-pcie f8000000.pcie: PCIe link training gen1 timeout!

The Armbian Rockchip64 PCIe patch stack is semantically unchanged between
the working 6.8 and failing 6.12 patch directories, leaving upstream
Rockchip host-driver changes as the next divergence to test.

One such change is the PERST/link-training timing.  Linux 6.8 enabled
Gen1 link training, released endpoint reset immediately, and then started
polling for link-up.  Linux 6.12 and newer add a 100 ms wait before
releasing PERST and another 100 ms reset-to-config wait after release
before polling.

Restore the 6.8 timing for RK3399 only.  Keep the newer PCIe reset-timing
waits for other Rockchip PCIe controllers.

Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@local>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
@@ -283,6 +283,8 @@ static void rockchip_pcie_set_power_limit(struct rockchip_pcie *rockchip)
 static int rockchip_pcie_host_init_port(struct rockchip_pcie *rockchip)
 {
 	struct device *dev = rockchip->dev;
+	bool rk3399 = of_device_is_compatible(dev->of_node,
+					      "rockchip,rk3399-pcie");
 	int err, i = MAX_LANE_NUM;
 	u32 status;
 
@@ -314,10 +316,14 @@ static int rockchip_pcie_host_init_port(struct rockchip_pcie *rockchip)
 	rockchip_pcie_write(rockchip, PCIE_CLIENT_LINK_TRAIN_ENABLE,
 			    PCIE_CLIENT_CONFIG);
 
-	msleep(PCIE_T_PVPERL_MS);
+	if (!rk3399)
+		msleep(PCIE_T_PVPERL_MS);
+
 	gpiod_set_value_cansleep(rockchip->perst_gpio, 1);
 
-	msleep(PCIE_RESET_CONFIG_WAIT_MS);
+	/* Preserve the working 6.8 RK3399 link-training/PERST timing. */
+	if (!rk3399)
+		msleep(PCIE_RESET_CONFIG_WAIT_MS);
 
 	/* 500ms timeout value should be enough for Gen1/2 training */
 	err = readl_poll_timeout(rockchip->apb_base + PCIE_CLIENT_BASIC_STATUS1,
-- 
2.43.0
